				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The 65816 has different banks for the program counter and everything else. To switch the program counter into a different bank, you use the JSL opcode. A subroutine called this way has to return with RTL instead of RTS. To change the data bank (used by absolute addressing modes), you need to use that push the program bank (PHK) and push and pop the data bank (PHB and PLB respectively). One common sequence is PHK immediately followed by PLB to access program and read-only data in one bank. There are also absolute long addressing modes and a long indirect mode [d],y that temporarily change the data bank just for one instruction. These long modes work not only for LDA and STA but also for other group 1 instructions (ORA AND EOR CMP ADC SBC).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

